As I said, I dont know your use case, but another way you can split this would be to determine if it is possible to dynamically split the encodings on another mutually exclusive attribute (gender was one). Like if you known the location of the person who is submitting the image, you can only try to match against people in the same region. Also, if you notice that 80% of your checks are dones against the same 20% of encodings, you can make a smaller set of only these and try to match there first with a more restrictive threshold and if it fails, match against the whole set.

