It used to be just the `np.append` which with the target area being a SwathDefinition in this case and now that lons/lats are `Dataset` objects (read: Masked Arrays) it causes a weird interaction where the result of the append is a `Dataset` but it doesn't have a `_mask` attribute. With the above change it is a proper masked array. **However**, it is an index array so there is no point in anything being masked and there is no proper `valid_output_index.filled(invalid_index_value)`. I'm writing this down so that any future fixes I make make sense. I'll continue looking for the right fix.

